            "answer_text": "Shiva Om Dear Friend, You have indeed asked a very interesting question. The orthodox Shaivaite will most vehemently shoot down your suggestion and consider a proposition like this blasphemous. However, the liberal Shaivaite will not take such a hard stance and rather will be blissfully unconcerned of what one is chanting. It makes no difference to him at all. These petty matters are meant only for narrow minds who get stuck in these inconsequential issues that the main subject at hand stays unadressed. I personally subscribe to the liberal group. All I ask is faith in the Rudraksha mala worn. As long as the person has unflinching faith in the mala he is free to chant what he feels like, go to any religious place he feels like. Curbing of a person\u2019s freedom does not fetch one true followers. If he is a Shaivaite by heart he will come back and if he is not he will move away. Let us give everybody the right to choose. I earnestly hope that my humble answer has been both meaningful and useful to you. Shivam Kalyanam. Prof.Dr. Manoj Kalantri. Ph.D, D.Sc, D.LIt Eshans Emporium ",
