            "answer_text": "Yes, there are no hard and fast rules for chanting Hare Krishna. You can chant on any mala, rosary, subha, on your fingers, any kind of beads made of glass, pearls, crystal, plastic, wood, gemstones, even ball bearings if you want. Devotees in Russian psychiatric jails used small bread balls pressed onto strands from their blankets. Most serious devotees chose Tulsi beads, but the mantra sounds the same whatever beads you use, or whether you don\u2019t use any beads at all. ",
